Journey Page My Programs

Description & Requirements

Description

You are supposed to have a system that controls some LEDs lighting sequence according to button pressing.

You can find the below kit's manual here.

Requirements

  1. Read System Requirements Specifications
    1. Description
      1. Hardware Requirements
        1. Four LEDs (LED0, LED1, LED2, LED3)
        2. One button (BUTTON0)
      2. Software Requirements
        1. Initially, all LEDs are OFF
        2. Once BUTTON0 is pressed, LED0 will be ON
        3. Each press further will make another LED is ON
        4. At the fifth press, LED0 will changed to be OFF
        5. Each press further will make only one LED is OFF
        6. This will be repeated forever
        7. The sequence is described below 
          1. Initially (OFF, OFF, OFF, OFF)
          2. Press 1 (ON, OFF, OFF, OFF)
          3. Press 2 (ON, ON, OFF, OFF)
          4. Press 3 (ON, ON, ON, OFF)
          5. Press 4 (ON, ON, ON, ON)
          6. Press 5 (OFF, ON, ON, ON)
          7. Press 6 (OFF, OFF, ON, ON)
          8. Press 7 (OFF, OFF, OFF, ON)
          9. Press 8 (OFF, OFF, OFF, OFF)
          10. Press 9 (ON, OFF, OFF, OFF)
    2. What to deliver
      1. Nothing is major
  2. Create a design document for your system
    1. Description
      1. From the previous requirements, create a design document for your system
      2. The design document should contain the following sections
        1. Project Title and your name
        2. Project Description
        3. Project flowchart, state machine, or sequence diagram
        4. Layered architecture
        5. Project Modules APIs (All APIs should return an error state)
        6. APIs flowcharts or state machine
    2. What to deliver
      1. Deliver a PDF document containing all the above details
  3. Implement all required drivers
    1. Description
      1. Implement all drivers that you mentioned in your design document
      2. Please stick to the APIs you mentioned in the design document
      3. Create a unit test for at least one driver against happy and worst-case scenarios
      4. The unit test may be just a main function that calls the driver's APIs with different inputs and validate the output on the simulator
    2. What to deliver
      1. Deliver the drivers with at least unit testing for one driver
  4. Implement the application
    1. Description
      1. Implement the main application flow as required in the requirements
    2. What to deliver
      1. Deliver the main application
  5. Test your application
    1. Description
      1. Test your main application against the happy and worst-case scenarios
      2. The application will be tested on Simulation (Mandatory)
      3. The application will be tested on the kit (Optional)
    2. What to deliver
      1. Deliver all project files
      2. Deliver a video (5 min max):
        1. Discuss your project design
        2. Test your application whether on Simulation or Hardware
